Dockerize TOMCAT

--This Dockerfile enables you to run tomcat in a docker container.

Steps :

--Create a folder(TOMCAT_DOCKER_HOME) and put the Dockerfile in that folder
--Take the Tomcat installation/tar and put it under the previously created folder inside a folder "tomcat"
--Build the Docker image under the folder using the command "docker build ."
--Finally run the image using the docker run command : "docker run --name=tomcat <image_name>"


Notes:

--Put your webapp under the folder : TOMCAT_DOCKER_HOME/tomcat/webapps
--Map the port 8080 to a local port
--Volumize the folder "tomcat/webapps" if you want to deploy apps locally

